Shimadzu to Set Up African Subsidiary Next Month, President Says

-- B y   M a s a t s u g u   H o r i e
-- 
2011-09-22T02:58:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/shimadzu-to-set-up-african-subsidiary-next-month-president-says.html
Shimadzu Corp. (7701) , a Japanese maker of
measuring instruments, will set up a subsidiary in  Africa  next
month and targets sales of $8.6 million in the year ending March
2013. President Akira Nakamoto made the announcement today at a
news conference in Kyoto, where the company is based.  To contact the reporter on this story:
堀江政嗣 in Osaka at 
 mhorie3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
